snippet.textDisplay:
Dana has a point about this probably being Yoel´s last chance at the title but c´mon don´t put this on Yoel only. Both fighters had to fight and not just one. It´s ridiculous to put blame on one fighter only.

Plus when he says that Adesanya fights to the level of his opponents and when they come at him he fights back, insinuating that´s its only Yoel´s fault or if had he attacked the fight would´ve been different he is only defending Adesanya because he is the youngest of both fighters, has the potential to be a star and has the longest time in the UFC since Yoel is closest to retiring.
Last time i checked when someone takes the fight to Yoel he also fights back and has great fights. Both fighters are to blame here: one for not backing up the talk after calling Yoel out and the other for missing yet another big opportunity that doesnt come along often in the UFC. Yoel was basically lucky Adesanya didnt want to wait for Paulo Costa and Darren Til and Kevin Gastelum don´t have many wins or hype at the moment.

Not defending Yoel because i actually wanted Adesanya to win but its not fair to criticize only one fighter, period.
